---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Honduras 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Honduras. Bay Islands diving paradise, Roatan expat community, affordable mainland living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Honduras"
  subheadline="Honduras offers Bay Islands diving paradise, Roatan established expat community, extremely affordable mainland living, and Caribbean lifestyle—Central America hidden retirement gem."
  heroImage="/images/countries/honduras-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Honduras</h2>
  <p>
    Honduras offers two distinct retirement options—Bay Islands (Roatan, Utila) with Caribbean diving lifestyle and established expat communities, or extremely affordable mainland living. Roatan has become a major retirement destination with good infrastructure.
  </p>

  <p>
    Roatan offers Caribbean island life with US-influenced services. Mainland cities like Copan Ruinas offer colonial charm near Mayan ruins. La Ceiba is gateway to Bay Islands. Tegucigalpa and San Pedro Sula have best mainland healthcare but less attractive for retirement.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Roatan has some facilities</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish; English on Bay Islands</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $900-2,000/month; very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Caribbean islands; diving; affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Pensionado:</strong> Attractive program with tax benefits</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Honduras Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Honduras healthcare is limited—concentrated in Tegucigalpa and San Pedro Sula. Hospital Honduras Medical Center and CEMESA are better mainland options. Roatan has Cornerstone Hospital with some expat-oriented services. Serious conditions require evacuation to US or Guatemala City.
  </p>

  <p>
    International insurance with US evacuation is essential for seniors. Many Roatan expats use Miami for serious healthcare needs. Mainland options are improving but limited for complex care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Evacuation Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Healthcare is limited throughout Honduras—Roatan has Cornerstone Hospital but complex care requires evacuation. Miami is common destination for Roatan residents. Plan for air ambulance coverage as standard part of health security.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Honduras offers attractive pensionado benefits:
  </p>

  <h3>Pensionado Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees with $1,500+/month guaranteed pension income. Benefits include duty-free import of household goods and vehicle. Tax exemptions on foreign income. Attractive program for qualifying retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Rentista Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with investment income—demonstrate $2,500+/month from investments. Similar benefits to pensionado.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    90-day visa-free for many nationalities. Extensions possible through immigration office in major cities.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Honduras:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pensionado visa:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Essential given limited local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> US (Miami) evacuation critical</li>
    <li><strong>Roatan:</strong> Island location increases evacuation importance</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Honduras</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with US evacuation is essential for Honduras seniors—local healthcare is limited even on Roatan. Plan must include air ambulance to Miami or Houston. Cash payment works for routine local care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Honduras, international coverage with US evacuation is essential:
  </p>

