    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Honduras are moderate given need for international coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Honduran private care is affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Consultations $25-50; very affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Americas-only:</strong> Skip worldwide coverage if not traveling globally</li>
    <li><strong>Miami evacuation:</strong> Direct flights from Roatan essential</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Diver, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month pension. Active diver, Roatan lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pensionado visa. Cigna Global with Miami evacuation and dive coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~$360/month. Caribbean diving; US healthcare accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Canadian Beach Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension CAD 3,200/month. West End, Roatan lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Cornerstone Hospital for routine; Miami for serious.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~$880/month combined. Island paradise; evacuation security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Budget Explorer, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,200/month Social Security. Mainland living, Copan Ruinas.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> IMG Global with evacuation. Cash payment for routine local care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> IMG ~$290/month. Mayan ruins; extreme affordability.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Honduras safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mixed—Bay Islands (Roatan, Utila) are generally safe with tourism-based economy. Mainland cities have higher crime rates. Roatan expat community is well-established and secure. Standard precautions apply. Many retirees live comfortably on Bay Islands.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Roatan really a good retirement option?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes for the right person—established expat community, Caribbean lifestyle, good diving, English widely spoken. Healthcare is limited (Cornerstone Hospital). Internet and services are good. Not as developed as Costa Rica but more affordable and authentic Caribbean.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Honduras?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very affordable—Roatan is more expensive than mainland but still reasonable. Mainland is extremely affordable. Budget $1,200-2,000/month for Roatan; $800-1,200 for mainland. Domestic help affordable. Good value for Caribbean lifestyle.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about healthcare on Roatan?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Limited—Cornerstone Hospital handles routine care and some emergencies. Complex cases require evacuation to Miami (direct flights available). Plan for evacuation as standard. Many expats maintain relationships with US doctors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes with evacuation coverage essential for Honduras.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Honduran authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
